Oh yes. It used to be wonderful to go there. And she used to only have an oil lamp in the kitchen and she'd a front room and there was gas in the front room and a big table and even as old as they were they daren't give a back answer to me grandma. She 
was crippled with rheumatism - she used to go with a stick. And she was the boss. Oh yes, I remember one - time when - I remember one time when - one of - me mother's sisters, Auntie Margaret, and she gave - she back answered to me grandma and me grandma 
c
ouldn't get to her so she tipped the table up on her. And walloped her with her stick because she couldn't get - near her. But - they - oh, they daren't give any cheek. No, they daren't. But her used to sit for hours at me grandmothers listening to her ta
lk - telling the stories of the war }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8159037\charrsid814818 years}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14037617\charrsid814818 
 and the countries and that that she'd travelled in. It used to be very, very interesting. Very interesting.
